To stop the Node.js server when the port is in use, you can use the following commands in your terminal (PowerShell):

Find the Process ID (PID) using the port:
powershell
netstat -ano | findstr :5000
This will show a line like TCP    0.0.0.0:5000    0.0.0.0:0    LISTENING    12345. The last number (e.g., 12345) is the PID.
Kill the process using that PID:
powershell
taskkill /PID 12345 /F
(Replace 12345 with the actual PID you found).

